  <refnamediv>
    <refname>cmd_analog_in_volt</refname>
    <refpurpose>Command to read in analog signal from a connected Arduino board</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>h :</term>
            <listitem><para> Board pointer, to indicate which board to use to differentiate one board from another</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>pin_no :</term>
            <listitem><para> Analog pin to measure the signal</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>val :</term>
            <listitem><para> Reading in the input voltage from 0-5V</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Arduino UNO board has 6 analog input ports (A0 to A5), the Arduino Mega board has 16 analog input ports (A0 to A15).
The 10 bits channels convert the analog input from 0 to 5 volts, to a digital value between 0 and 1023. This function scale the reading to 0-5 so the user could get the measured voltage directly
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
h = open_serial(1,9,115200)
val = cmd_analog_in_volt(h,9)
close_serial(h)

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

